description: SM-HighLevel: Command refused, stepper motor is running
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  Command refused, stepper motor is currently running.<newline/>Meaning: Command is only allowed (_switchAccCurve) or has wrong parameters (opposite sign of run direction)  while motor is running.<newline/>Cure:    Check and correct your code.

description: SM-HighLevel: Microstep starting mode out of range
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  Microstep starting mode out of range.<newline/>Meaning: Wrong acceleration curve.<newline/>Cure:    Check your curve definition and correct it.

description: SM-HighLevel: Stepper motor speed level out of range
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  Speed level out of range.<newline/>Meaning: Speedlevel > max. speed level defined in acceleration curve.<newline/>Cure:    Check your speedlevel parameter in your command.

description: SM-HighLevel: Stepper motor current out of range
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  Current out of range.<newline/>Meaning: Current parameter smaller than min current defined in 'sm397xPublic.h'   or   > 100.<newline/>Cure:    Check your current parameters in your command.

description: SM-HighLevel: No stepper motor acceleration curve loaded
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  No acceleration curve loaded.<newline/>Meaning: Before starting any stepper motor, an acceleration curve must be loaded.<newline/>Cure:    Load acceleration curve.

description: SM-HighLevel: No valid stepper motor acceleration curve
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:   No valid acceleration curve.<newline/>Meaning: Invalid pointer to acceleration curve that should be used for running.<newline/>Cure:    Correct your load_curve command.

description: SM-HighLevel: Steps to target error
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  Steps to target error.<newline/>Meaning: Command setStepsToTarget() while motor is running:  less steps than number of speed levels in curve.<newline/>         Command setLevelRepeatFactor() while motor is running:  target cannot be reached, motor will stop later.<newline/>Cure:    Software bugfixing.

description: SM-HighLevel: Set steps while braking stepper motor
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  Try to set steps to target while braking.<newline/>Meaning: It is not allowed to call command 'setStepsToTarget()' while motor is currently breaking.<newline/>Cure:    Software bugfixing.

description: SM-HighLevel: Invalid level repeat factor for stepper motor
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  Invalid level repeat factor(0).<newline/>Meaning: This level repeat factor makes no sense.<newline/>Cure:    Software bugfixing.

description: SM-HighLevel: Unknown stepper motor library error
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  Unknown stepper motor library error.<newline/>Meaning: this stepper motor library error is not known in stepper motor high level methods. Software modules don't fit together.<newline/>Cure:    Software bugfixing.

description: SM-HighLevel: Stepper motor timeout
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  timeout occurred while waiting for end of any action.<newline/>Meaning: Motor has not finished its action when timeout time is over. This means either the timeoout time is too short for this action or the motor has any problem e.g. mechanical or acceleration problems and therefore does not reach any sensor.<newline/>Cure:    Check for the cause and correct it.

description: SM-HighLevel: Wrong stepper motor run direction
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  wrong run direction given as parameter to any command.<newline/>Meaning: e.g. if motor is still running in positiv run direction, and then gets any command which would result in a negativ run direction <newline/>Cure:    Select command parameters carefully, Software bugfixing.

description: SM-HighLevel: Wrong stepper motor speedlevel
explanation: Reason:  Stepper Motor HighLevel:  wrong parameter speedlevel.<newline/>Meaning: This speedlevel is not allowed for this command.<newline/>Cure:    Select practicable speedlevel for this action.

description: Scanhead-Control: Stepper motor Left Distance: Not Connected.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control  Module:  Stepper motor SM-Left Distance(M511) not detected.<newline/>Meaning:  SM-Left Distance(M511) not connected or defective or motor cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    connect SM-Left Distance(M511) or replace cable/SM-Left Distance.

description: Scanhead-Control: Stepper motor Left Distance: Test Cosine Phase failed.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control Module: Stepper motor SM-Left Distance(M511) cosine-phase test failed.<newline/>Meaning:   SM-Left Distance(M511) defective or motor cable defective.<newline/>Cure:   Replace IP platform assembly.

description: Scanhead-Control: Stepper motor Left Distance: Test Sine Phase failed.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control Module: Stepper motor SM-Left Distance(M511) sine-phase test failed.<newline/>Meaning:   SM-Left Distance(M511) defective or motor cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    replace cable/SM-Left Distance.

description: Scanhead-Control: Stepper motor Right Distance: Not Connected.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control  Module:  Stepper motor SM-Right Distance(M510) not detected.<newline/>Meaning:  SM-Right Distance(M510) not connected or defective or motor cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    connect SM-Right Distance(M510) or replace cable/SM-Right Distance.

description: Scanhead-Control: Stepper motor Right Distance: Test Cosine Phase failed.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control Module: Stepper motor SM-Right Distance(M510) cosine-phase test failed.<newline/>Meaning:   SM-Right Distance(M510) defective or motor cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    replace cable/SM-Right Distance.

description: Scanhead-Control: Stepper motor Right Distance: Test Sine Phase failed.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control Module: Stepper motor SM-Right Distance(M510) sine-phase test failed.<newline/>Meaning:   SM-Right Distance(M510) defective or motor cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    replace cable/SM-Right Distance.

description: Scanhead-Control: Supply voltage Out of range.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control Module: The supply voltage of the Scanhead-CTRL node is below a level which allows a reliable operation of the motors.<newline/>Meaning: Scanhead-Ctrl Node(B572) or Flexboard(B580) or Distribution board(575) defective or PowerSupply unit(B101) defective or cables between both units defective.<newline/>Cure: Check/Replace Scanhead-Ctrl Node(B572) or Flexboard(B580) or Distribution board(575) or MainPowerSupply(B101) unit or cables between both units.

description: Scanhead-Control: Driver defective
explanation: Meaning:  Scanhead-Control Module: One of the hardware drivers for the distance stepper motors(M510/M511) is defective.<newline/>Cure: Replace Scanhead-Ctrl Node(B572)

description: Scanhead-Control: Left Precision switch not connected
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control  Module:   Left Precision Switch(S506) not detected.<newline/>Meaning: Left Precision Switch(S506) not connected or defective or cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    connect Switch(S506) to ST1 on Scanhead-Ctrl Board or replace cable/Switch(S506).

description: Scanhead-Control: Left Distance  Home-Pos Sensor not connected.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control Module: Left Distance  Home-Pos Sensor(B570) not detected.<newline/>Meaning: Left Distance  Home-Pos Sensor(B570) not connected or defective or sensor cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    connect Sensor(B570) to ST2 on Scanhead-Ctrl Board or replace cable/Sensor(B570)..

description: Scanhead-Control: Right Precision switch not connected
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control  Module:   Right Precision Switch(S505) not detected.<newline/>Meaning: Right Precision Switch(S505) not connected or defective or cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    connect Switch(S505) to ST11 on Scanhead-Ctrl Board or replace cable/Switch(S505).

description: Scanhead-Control:  Right Distance  Home-Pos Sensor not connected.
explanation: Reason:  Scanhead-Control Module: Right Distance  Home-Pos Sensor(B569) not detected.<newline/>Meaning: Right Distance  Home-Pos Sensor(B569) not connected or defective or sensor cable defective.<newline/>Cure:    connect Sensor(B569) to ST12 on Scanhead-Ctrl Board or replace cable/Sensor(B569)..

description: Lamp Fan Speed RPM Too Low
explanation: Reason: Lamp Fan Speed RPM Signal Too Low<newline/>Meaning: Fan is stopped, blocked or unconnected. Fan is defect or Electronic board defective at fan circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Check fan openings for blocking, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Electronic Fan Speed RPM Too Low
explanation: Reason: Electronic Fan Speed RPM Signal Too Low, fan is stopped or blocked<newline/>Meaning: Fan is stopped, blocked or unconnected. Fan is defect or Electronic board defective at fan circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Check fan openings for blocking, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Lamp Fan Speed RPM measurement timeout in passive Test
explanation: Reason: Lamp Fan Speed RPM Signal not valid. Not enough valid measured values.<newline/>Meaning: Measurement timed out during passive Test. Fan is not correctly connected, Fan is defect or Electronic board defective at fan circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Electronic Fan Speed RPM measurement timeout in passive Test
explanation: Reason: Electronic Fan Speed RPM Signal not valid, measurement timed out in passive Test. Not enough valid measured values.<newline/>Meaning: Measurement timed out during passive Test. Fan is not correctly connected, Fan is defect or Electronic board defective at fan circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Simmer Current Start failed after max. number of retries
explanation: Reason: Simmer Current Start failed after maximum number of retries.<newline/>Meaning: Erasure Lamp is worn out, defect, or unable to start the simmer mode and the flash cycle. <newline/>Electronic board may be defective at simmer ingnition ciruitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer, Check cables and Erasure Lamp connections, Replace Erasure Lamp, Replace Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Simmer Current Protection failed to react after max. Time Limit
explanation: Reason: Simmer Current Protection failed to react after needed max. Time Limit.<newline/>Meaning: It does not switch off the Simmer Current in the needed time. Active output of error message from HW-Ver. 2 on. Before a warning is generated. Electronic defect at Simmer Current Protection circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Lamp Fan Speed RPM measurement timeout in Active Test
explanation: Reason: Lamp Fan Speed RPM Signal not valid, measurement timed out in active Test. Not enough valid measured values.<newline/>Meaning: Measurement timed out during active Test. Fan is not correctly connected, Fan is defect or Electronic board defective at fan circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Electronic Fan Speed RPM measurement timeout in Active Test
explanation: Reason: Electronic Fan Speed RPM Signal not valid, measurement timed out in active Test. Not enough valid measured values.<newline/>Meaning: Measurement timed out during active Test. Fan is not correctly connected, Fan is defect or Electronic board defective at fan circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Simmer current cut off during active operation mode
explanation: Reason: Simmer current cut off during active flashing operation mode.<newline/>Meaning: Missing of Flashing Time possible. Erasure Result not in valid operation range.<newline/>Check Infocounters if the error repeats in a high rate.<newline/>Cure: If the events of this error (see infocounters) during the same period of cycles increase  then replace Erasure Lamp.

description: Continuous Liftetime Test Cycle of the Flash Erasure Unit blocked due to connection of CAN
explanation: Reason: Continuous Liftetime Test Cycle of the Flash Erasure Unit blocked due to connection of CAN.<newline/>Meaning: The SW in the Flash Erasure Unit is a special version for autonomous lifetimetest cycles. This cycles  run isolated from the PC. The trigger for the situation experienced here is, that the connection via CAN to a PC is active like in a complete Digitizer. And so the Flash Erasure Unit is not in the right setting to proceed the lifetime test. The reaction of the SW is that no lifetime test cycles start for safety. <newline/>Cure: Load new Software, restart.

description: FEU Electronic Temp Over Limit
explanation: Reason: Monitoring of Temperature finds a too high Temperature at Erasure Unit inside. <newline/>Meaning: The cooling is hindered or defect. Future hardware overtemperature stop is likely. No safe Erasure Operation allowed. <newline/>Cure: Check Fans, Fan Airflow and Openings, Environment Temperature.

description: Flashing terminated by timeout. Stop Flashlight Cmd missing, Another SW Module failed to react after max. Time Limit.
explanation: Reason: Communication to Flash Erasure Unit disturbed. Or another SW-Module does not react.<newline/>Meaning: The Flash Cycle was started and not ended by a received command but via timeout. <newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer, Load new Software, Replace Erasure Unit.

description: Electronic Temperatur Sensor Offset Failure, possible wire break
explanation: Reason: Temperature sensor values invalid.<newline/>Meaning: The values indicate also a wire break, or defect in the electronic inside the Erasure Unit.   <newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Operate at specified environment temperature. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Electronic Temperatur Sensor out of Range
explanation: Reason: Temperature sensor values out of the valid measurement and calculation range.<newline/>Meaning: Calculation of raw values to temperature degrees failed. Raw values are out of range.   <newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Operate at specified environment temperature. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Flash Voltage sensed out of Range Limit
explanation: Reason: Flash Voltage measured out of the valid operation range limits.<newline/>Meaning: Flash Energy is decreased. Electronic is defect.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Load new Software. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Trig Voltage sensed out of Range Limit
explanation: Reason: Trigger Voltage measured out of the valid operation range limits.<newline/>Meaning: Trigger Energy is decreased. Electronic defect.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Load new Software. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Prepare Flashing  failed due to a error detected at the condition check
explanation: Reason: Command to Prepare Flashing failed as at the check for operation conditions of the Erasure Unit a parameter is outside of the valid operation range limits.<newline/>Meaning: Flashing could not be started with valid operation conditions.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Retry Erasure Operation. Load new Software. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Flash Voltage sensed out of Range Limit at Flash active On
explanation: Reason: Flash Voltage measured out of the valid operation range limits during the active Flashing On period.<newline/>Meaning: Flash Energy is decreased. Electronic is defect.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Load new Software. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Start Flashlight failed due to a error detected at the condition check
explanation: Reason: Command to Start Flashlight failed as at the check for operation conditions of the Erasure Unit a parameter is outside of the valid operation range limits.<newline/>Meaning: Flashing could not be started with valid operation conditions.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Retry Erasure Operation. Load new Software. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Counted Flash Pulses during Cycle are out of Range Limit
explanation: Reason: During the active Flashing On period the expected and the measured value of counted Flash Pulses is outside of the valid operation range limits.<newline/>Meaning: Flashing could not be proceeded with valid operation conditions.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Retry Erasure Operation. Load new Software. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Erasure Speed Calculation impossible due to invalid used input parameters
explanation: Reason: Parameter for the calculaton is outside of the valid operation range limits.<newline/>Meaning: Flash movement speed could not be calculated with valid parameter.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Retry Erasure Operation. Load new Software. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Warning: SW Version for Liftetime Test Cycle present in Flash Erasure Unit
explanation: Reason: SW Version for Liftetime Test Cycle presently loaded into Flash Erasure Unit. <newline/>Meaning: This is a Warning Message, No Error.<newline/>Cure: Check if you want to perform a lifetime Test Cycle. If so this is the right SW.

description: Warning: Lamp Fan Speed RPM Out Of Tolerance
explanation: Reason: Lamp Fan Speed RPM Signal Out Of Tolerance. <newline/>Meaning: Fan speed is not in expected tolerance range. The fan connections inside can be mixed up, too.<newline/>Cure: Watch for increased number of this warning. This indicates a weak fan.

description: Warning: Electronic Fan Speed RPM Out Of Tolerance
explanation: Reason: Electronic Fan Speed RPM Signal Out Of Tolerance. <newline/>Meaning: Fan speed is not in expected tolerance range. The fan connections inside can be mixed up, too.<newline/>Cure: Watch for increased number of this warning. This indicates a weak fan.

description: Warning: Simmer Current Protection failed to react after max. Time Limit
explanation: Reason: Simmer Current Protection failed to react after max. Time Limit. <newline/>Meaning: The electronic circuitry does not switch off the Simmer Current in the needed time. Active for error message from HW-Ver. 2 on. Before a warning is generated.<newline/>Cure: Use the correct Hardware Version. Change Erasure Unit.

description: Warning: FEU Electronic Temp Over Limit
explanation: Reason: Monitoring of Temperature finds a high Temperature at Erasure Unit inside. <newline/>Meaning: The cooling is hindered or defect. Future hardware overtemperature stop of the Erasure Unit is possible if the temperature still rises. <newline/>Cure: Check Fans, Fan Airflow and Openings, Environment Temperature.

description: Warning:Lamp Fan Speed RPM Too Low. Occured during Erasure Operation. This current operation is finished normally.
explanation: Reason: Lamp Fan Speed RPM Signal Too Low<newline/>Meaning: Fan is stopped, blocked or unconnected. Fan is defect or Electronic board defective at fan circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Check fan openings for blocking, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Warning: Electronic Fan Speed RPM Too Low. Occured during Erasure Operation. This current operation is finished normally.
explanation: Reason: Electronic Fan Speed RPM Signal Too Low, fan is stopped or blocked<newline/>Meaning: Fan is stopped, blocked or unconnected. Fan is defect or Electronic board defective at fan circuitry.<newline/>Cure: Restart digitzer, Check fan openings for blocking, Change Flash Erasure Unit.

description: Warning: Electronic Temperatur Sensor out of tolerance Range
explanation: Reason: The test of measurement failed as the valid range at the ADC is violated. <newline/>Meaning: Internal error in SW, or defect electronic.<newline/>Cure: Restart Digitzer. Load new Software. Replace Erasure Unit

description: Warning: Flash Voltage sensed out of tolerance Range
explanation: Reason: Flash Voltage measured is not exact at the target value.<newline/>Meaning: Flash Energy is not exact at target value. Electronic has large tolerances.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Warning: Trig Voltage sensed out of tolerance Range
explanation: Reason: Trigger Voltage measured is not exact at the target value.<newline/>Meaning: Flash Energy is not exact at target value. Electronic has large tolerances.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Warning: Flash Voltage sensed out of tolerance Range at Flash active On
explanation: Reason: Flash Voltage measured is not exact at the target value.<newline/>Meaning: Flash Energy is not exact at target value. Electronic has large tolerances.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Counted Flash Pulses during Cycle are out of Tolerance
explanation: Reason: Flash Pulses Counted are not exact at the target value.<newline/>Meaning: Flash Energy is not exact at target value. Electronic has tolerances.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Counted Flash Pulses during Simmer Start are out of Tolerance, and different from initiated Pulses
explanation: Reason: Flash Pulses Counted are not exact at the target value.<newline/>Meaning: Flash Start Procedure is not exact at target value. Electronic has tolerances.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Warning: Simmer Current Sensor signals Status SimmerOn at passive selftest
explanation: Reason: Sensor Signal not at the expected  target value.<newline/>Meaning: Simmer Current signal is On even if switched Off. Electronic has tolerances or is sporadic broken or defect at this circuitry. If defect, additional errors will be noticable.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Counted Flash Pulses during Startup. Sensor signals Pulses at passive selftest
explanation: Reason: Flash Pulses Counted are not exact at the target value.<newline/>Meaning: Pulses measured even if switched off.  Electronic has tolerances.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Warning: Elabel Access Failed at Flash Pulse Counter
explanation: Reason: Flash Pulses Counter could not saved into Elabel.<newline/>Meaning: Pulses in the Elabel not updated. Electronic has tolerances.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Warning: Wrong Parameter in command or unexpected command
explanation: Reason: Command received via communication, which is not processed.<newline/>Meaning: A wrong command was initiated, or received at the wrong time, or with wrong parameters. Possible SW-Fault, or Communication Error.<newline/>Cure: Watch Infocounters for Erasure Unit Errors.

description: Cass-Handling,  Opener Drive:  Timeout while waitting for end of any action.
