description: TagReader hardware too old
explanation: CassetteReader Module.<newline/>Meaning: <newline/>TagReader hardware too old for current DX-S Software.<newline/>Reason:<newline/>CassetteReader(B258) hardware (and firmware) is not capable to access the calibration data stored on the IP. <newline/>Cure:<newline/>Please refer to the release note of this DX-S software version for the correct revision of the tagreader and then replace the CassetteReader(B258) unit.

description: Cannot deliver message +ReadOK, but IPDATA version not supported+
explanation: CassetteReader Module.<newline/>Meaning: <newline/>IPData at cassette/IP is too new for this software version of DX-S.<newline/>Reason:<newline/>Most likely, this is a new cassette that might carry a flexible IP, which would damage the scanhead, if processed. <newline/>Cure:<newline/>Check your cassette/IP - if this IP can be processed in your digitizer, please ask for a software update, if not, please feed this cassette into an appropriate digitizer.

description: Cannot allocatge space for this message +ReadOK, but IPDATA version not supported+
explanation: CassetteReader Module.<newline/>Meaning: <newline/>Cannot send message.<newline/>Reason:<newline/>Out of memory.<newline/>Cure:<newline/>No cure / you have to reset the digitzer.

description: The PLD on the CCD board is not accessible.
explanation: Meaning: The accessibility test of the PLD failed.<newline/>Reason: The communication between the microcontroller and the PLD does not work correctly, because<newline/>	(i) the PLD is not in the correct status to cope with the test correctly.<newline/>	(ii) of hardware problems (device and cabling)  <newline/>Cure: Retry the accessibility test of the PLD  (up to three times)
column5: if the test then still does not work, reset the PLD and retry the test
column6: if the test then still does not work, check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Check the cable connections between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead) and restart the Digitizer. If the test then still does not work replace successively (i) the three cables mentioned above, (ii) the ScanHead, (iii) the SHI board.

description: The EEPROM on the CCD board is not accessible.
explanation: Meaning: The accessibility test of the EEPROM on the CCD board failed.<newline/>Reason: The communication between the microcontroller and the EEPROM on the CCD board does not work correctly, because<newline/>	(i) the EEPROM is not in the correct status to cope with the test correctly.<newline/>	(ii) of hardware problems (device and cabling) <newline/>Cure: Retry the accessibility test of the EEPROM on the CCD
column5: if the test then still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The EEPROM on the Line Light Source board is not accessible.
explanation: Meaning: The accessibility test of the EEPROM on the LLS board failed.<newline/>Reason: The communication between the microcontroller and the EEPROM on the LLS board does not work correctly, because<newline/>	(i) the EEPROM is not in the correct status to cope with the test correctly.<newline/>	(ii) of hardware problems (device and cabling) <newline/>Cure: Retry the accessibility test of the EEPROM on the LLS
column5: if the test then still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The A/D converters were not initialized correctly.
explanation: Meaning: The AD converters were not initialized correctly.<newline/>Reason: The initial data could not be written correctly into the A/D converter registers.<newline/>Cure: Retry the initialization of the AD converter. If the initialization then still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The Line Light Source was not initialized correctly.
explanation: Meaning: The LLS was not initialized correctly because at least one value of the LD data was not in the specified range.<newline/>Reason: (i) The LD data could not be read correctly form the EEPROM(LLS), or <newline/>	(ii) At least one value stored in the EEPROM(LLS) is not correct		<newline/>Cure: Retry the initialization of the LLS. If the initialization still does not work: (i) Check the data stored in the EEPROM of the LLS (header and LD data). (ii) Check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The FPGA was not  initialized correctly.
explanation: Meaning: The FPGA was not initialized (i.e. configured) correctly.<newline/>Reason: (i) The FPGA has not been loaded, (ii) The external clock signal was not set correctly.		<newline/>Cure: Reload the FPGA and retry the initialization of the FPGA. If the initialization then still does not work check the hardware (FPGA, external clock signal).<newline/>Service:  Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace the SHI board.

description: The test of the FPGA was not successful.
explanation: Meaning: The test of the FPGA was not successful <newline/>Reason: The read/write access of the RAM's was not successful.	<newline/>Cure: Reset the system and retry the test of the FPGA. If the test then still does not work check the hardware (FPGA and RAM's, external clock signal).<newline/>Service: Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the SHI board, (ii)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (iii) the ScanHead.

description: The 'ready'-signal has a wrong value before starting the scanning process.
explanation: Meaning: The 'ready'-signal has a wrong value before starting the scanning process. The PLD communicates the status of the scan to the ScannerControl task (on the microcontroller) via the value of the 'ready'-signal. The value is zero during a scan and one at any time else. If this value is zero when no scan is being performed a wrong status has been set. <newline/>Reason: (i) The PLD has not been initialized correctly. <newline/>	(ii) The PLD is scanning when the 'ready'-signal is checked. This erroneous scan has either been started by the PLD or triggered by the ScannerControl task.<newline/>Cure: Initialize the PLD again (e.g. by restarting the system).<newline/>Service:  Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead,  (iii) the SHI board

description: The register of the PLD was not loaded correctly.
explanation: Meaning: The  register of the PLD was not loaded correctly before the scan.	<newline/>Reason: The corresponding software routine was not performed correctly. <newline/>Cure: Reset the system and load the PLD again (e.g.  by performing a scan).

description: A Flush FIFO overflow occurred during the scan.
explanation: Meaning: The scanning process finished with a flush fifo overflow.<newline/>Reason: Data was not transferred correctly from the PLD to the FPGA during a scan	<newline/>Cure: The hardware elements of the data transfer (i.e. the PLD and the FPGA)	have to be examined.<newline/>Service: Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (ii) the SHI board, (iii) the ScanHead.

description: A Flush FIFO underrun occurred during the scan.
explanation: Meaning: The scanning process finished with a flush fifo underrun. <newline/>Reason: Data was not transferred correctly from the PLD to the FPGA during a scan.	<newline/>Cure: The hardware elements of the data transfer (i.e. the PLD and the FPGA) have to be examined.<newline/>Service:  Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (ii) the SHI board, (iii) the ScanHead.

description: The signatures of the flush fifo (1 and 2) were not identical after the scanning process.
explanation: Meaning: The signatures of the flush fifo (1 and 2) were not identical after the scanning process. 	<newline/>The signatures 1 and 2 provide a check of the correct transmission of the scanned pixels from the CCD board to the FPGA via the flush fifo. If the transmission was correct the signatures are identical, if the pixels were not transmitted correctly the signatures have two different values. <newline/>Reason: Data was not transferred correctly from the PLD to the FPGA during a scan.<newline/>Cure: The hardware elements of the data transfer (i.e. the PLD and the FPGA) have to be examined.<newline/>Service:  Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (ii) the SHI board,  (iii) the ScanHead.

description: A parameter value was not set correctly.
explanation: Meaning: A parameter value could was not set correctly. (via the external control).<newline/>Reason: (i) Communication problems, or (ii) the parmeter was set in the wrong state of the SCC state table, or (iii) a wrong index was passed from ScannerControlProxy to ScannerControl (i.e. the command could not be interpreted).<newline/>Cure: Verify the communication, the SCC state and reset the parameter value.

description: The scanning procces failed because it ended by registrating a time out.
explanation: Meaning: The scanning procces failed because it ended by registrating a time out.<newline/>Reason: (i) A wrong scan parameter set was sent to the PLD. (ii) communication problem (i.e. the Scanner Control task did not receive the 'scan ready'-signal. (iii) The PLD did not scan correctly.<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the parameter set sent to the PLD, (ii) the communication hardware, (iii) the PLD.<newline/>Service: Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead,  (iii) the SHI board

description: The EPROM(CCD) could not accomplish an operation.
explanation: Meaning: A hardware operation in the EEPROM(CCD) was not accomplished within the defined time out. During accesses of tasks to the EEPROM on the CCD board hardware operations have to be performed.<newline/>Some of these operations have relatively long perfomance time (e.g. write a value into a defined cell) and therefore the EEPROM communicates the completion of the operation to the task via a 'ready'-signal
column5: the task has to wait for the 'ready'-signal before accessing the EEPROM again. The EEPROM does not work properly if this 'ready'-signal does not arrive within a defined timeout. In case of logging an error message the byte received from the device is given as parameter.<newline/>Reason: The EEPROM(CCD) could not handle a succession of operations successfully. 	<newline/>Cure: Reset the system and try the operation again. In case of repeated failure check the hardware.

description: The EPROM(LLS) could not accomplish an operation.
explanation: Meaning: A hardware operation in the EEPROM(LLS) was not accomplished within the defined time out.<newline/>During accesses of tasks to the EEPROM on the CCD board hardware operations have to be performed.<newline/>Some of these operations have relatively long perfomance time (e.g. write a value into a defined cell) and therefore the EEPROM communicates the completion of the operation to the task via a 'ready'-signal
column5: the task has to wait for the 'ready'-signal before accessing the EEPROM again.<newline/>The EEPROM does not work properly if this 'ready'-signal does not arrive within a defined timeout.<newline/>Reason: The EEPROM(LLS) could not handle a succession of operations successfully. <newline/>Cure: Reset the system and try the operation again. In case of repeated failure check the hardware.

description: A wrong LD number was (i) input, or (ii) read from the EEPROM(LLS)
explanation: Meaning: The number of the laser diode (i) input via the external control, or (ii) read from the EEPROM(LLS) is not valid.<newline/>Reason: (i) Wrong input via the external control, (ii) communication problems, (iii) wrong value stored in the EEPROM (LLS).<newline/>Cure: (i) Set the number of the laser diode again,<newline/>	(ii) verify the communication PC - embedded system, <newline/>	(iii) verify the value stored in the EEPROM(LLS).

description: The basic write/read test of the left AD converter failed.
explanation: Meaning: The basic write/read test of the left AD converter failed.<newline/>Reason: The communication between the microcontroller and the left A/D converter on the CCD board does not work correctly.	<newline/>Cure: Retry the accessibility test
column5: if the test then still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The basic write/read test of the right AD converter failed.
explanation: Meaning: The basic write/read test of the right AD converter failed.<newline/>Reason: The communication between the microcontroller and the right A/D converter on the CCD board does not work correctly.		<newline/>Cure: Retry the accessibility test
column5: if the test then still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The basic write/read test of the both AD converters failed.
explanation: Meaning: The basic write/read test of both AD converters failed.<newline/>Reason: The communication between the microcontroller and both A/D converters on the CCD board does not work correctly.<newline/>Cure: Retry the accessibility test
column5: if the test then still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The Gain factor exceeds the limit 12.
explanation: Meaning: The Gain factor exceeds the limit 12.	<newline/>Reason: The set of the scanning/matching parameters is not entirely correct.<newline/>Cure: Check the scanning/matching parameters and find out which parameter(s) does(do) not fit to a correct set.

description: Data could not be written correctly into the EEPROM(LLS).
explanation: Meaning: The EEPROM(LLS) could not write the data into the defined memory cell.<newline/>Reason: The time delay between two write cycles is too short for the device.	<newline/>Cure: Augment the time delay between two write cycles and retry writing the data.

description: The basic write test of the EEPROM on the LLS board failed. Reading from the device may still work (the data read from the device is verified separately). It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The basic write test of the EEPROM on the LLS board failed. Reading from the device may still work (the data read from the device is verified separately).  It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed. <newline/>Reason: (i) The device is defect (reading from the device may still work). (ii)	The communication between the microcontroller and the EEPROM on the CCD board does not work correctly.<newline/>Cure: Retry the basic write test of the EEPROM(LLS)
column5: if the test then still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: This is only a warning message. (i) As long as no data is written into the device (e.g. calibration lines) no problems will arise because the data read out of the device (during the start-up) is verified separately. Normal use of the device is possible. (ii) If a calibration has to be done (which implies that data has to be written into the device) the ScanHead has to be replaced before.

description: Data could not be written correctly into the EEPROM on the CCD board.
explanation: Meaning: The EEPROM(CCD) could not write the data into the defined memory cell(s).<newline/>Reason: The time delay between two write cycles is too short for the device.	<newline/>Cure: Augment the time delay between two write cycles and retry writing the data.

description: Data could not be erased in the EEPROM on the LLS board.
explanation: Meaning: The data in the memory cell(s) could not be erased.<newline/>Reason: (i) The communication between the microcontroller and the EEPROM on the LLS board does not work correctly, or<newline/>	(ii) The EEPROM(LLS) has a hardware problem.	<newline/>Cure: Retry to erase data in the EEPROM(LLS)
column5: if that still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).

description: The amount of LD's  is wrong
explanation: Meaning: The amount of laser diodes (e.g. read form the EEPROM(LLS)) was is not correct. Therefore, during the initialization,<newline/>	(i) the current data of the LLS diodes was not loaded from the EEPROM(LLS), and <newline/>	(ii) the LLS was not armed. 	<newline/>Reason: (i) The communication with the EEPROM(LLS) does not work properly.<newline/>	(ii) The EEPROM(LLS) has not been initialized (correctly).<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the data saved in the EEPROM(LLS), (ii) whether the amount of LD's is read out of the EEPRO(LLS) and then processed correctly, (ii) the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The LLS could not be armed for the next scan.
explanation: Meaning: The LLS could not be armed for the next scan.<newline/>Reason: (i) The amount of LD's (read from the EPROMM(LLS)) is wrong, (ii) Communication problems			<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the data stored in the EEPROM(LLS), (ii) the hardware.<newline/>Reset the system and try to arm the LLS again.

description: The value of the preliminary current for one LD read from the EEPROM(LLS) is out of the defined range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the preliminary current for one LD read from the EEPROM(LLS) is out of the defined range.	<newline/>Reason: (i) The communication with the EEPROM(LLS) does not work properly.<newline/>	(ii) The EEPROM(LLS) has not been initialized (correctly).	<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the data stored in the EEPROM(LLS),<newline/>	(ii) the hardware.<newline/>	Reset the system and read the LLS data from the EEPROM(LLS) again.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The value of the operational current for one LD read from the EEPROM(LLS) is out of the defined range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the operational current for one LD read from the EEPROM(LLS) is out of the defined range.	<newline/>Reason: (i) The communication with the EEPROM(LLS) does not work properly.<newline/>	(ii) The EEPROM(LLS) has not been initialized (correctly).	<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the data stored in the EEPROM(LLS), (ii) the hardware.<newline/>	Reset the system and read the LLS data from the EEPROM(LLS) again.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: The CCD board could not be armed for the next scan.
explanation: Meaning: The CCD board could not be armed for the next scan.<newline/>Reason: At least one of the electronic devices (A/D converters, D/A converters, PLD) could not be armed for the next scan. 	<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the data set used by the software to arm the devices, (ii) the hardware (i.e. determine more specifically the electronic devices that cause problems)
column5: <newline/>Reset the system and try to arm the CCD board again.

description: The header version of a data set is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The header version of a data set stored (or to be stored) in the EEPROM(CCD) is not defined.<newline/>Reason: (i) Wrong data has been written into the EEPROM(CCD), or (ii) a wrong version has been set in the header 	<newline/>Cure: (i) Check the data stored in the EEPROM(CCD), (ii) set the correct header version in the data to be stored in the EEPROM(CCD).

description: The header type of a data set is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The header type of a data set stored (or to be stored) in the EEPROM(CCD) is not defined.<newline/>Reason: (i) Wrong data has been written into the EEPROM(CCD), or (ii) a wrong type has been set in the header 	<newline/>Cure: (i) Check the data stored in the EEPROM(CCD), (ii) set the correct header type in the data to be stored in the EEPROM(CCD).

description: The binning mode value is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The binning mode value is not defined. The defined values are 1, 2 and 3.<newline/>Reason: (i) A wrong binning mode value has been set (in the software).<newline/>	(ii) A wrong data has been written into the EEPROM(CCD). <newline/>Cure: (i) Check the corresponding SW routines and set the correct binning mode number.<newline/>	(ii) Check the data stored in the EEPROM(CCD) and eventually correct the header.

description: The number for selecting one of the two A/D converters is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The number for selecting one of the two A/D converters is not defined.<newline/>Reason: A wrong selection number has been set. 	<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines and set the correct selection number.

description: The number for selecting an A/D converter register cell is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The number for selecting an A/D converter register cell is not defined.<newline/>Reason: A wrong selection number has been set. 	<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines and set the correct selection number.

description: The number for selecting a D/A converter register cell is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The number for selecting a D/A converter register cell is not defined.<newline/>Reason: A wrong selection number has been set. 	<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines and set the correct selection number.

description: The number for selecting a calibration line is not defined.
explanation: <newline/>Meaning: The number for selecting a calibration line is not defined.<newline/>Reason: A wrong calibration line number has been input (via the external control).<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines and set the correct selection number.

description: The number for selecting a calibration line type is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The number for selecting a calibration line type is not defined.<newline/>Reason: A wrong calibration line type has been input (via the external control). 	<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines and set the correct selection number.

description: A calibration line could not be sent correctly from the PC to the microcontroller.
explanation: Meaning: The calibration line could not be sent correctly from the PC to the microcontroller. <newline/>Reason: (difo) transmission error 	<newline/>Cure: Check the data transmission (via difo) and the data storage on the PC and in the microcontroller. Retry the data transmission.

description: A calibration line could not be sent correctly from the microcontroller to the PC.
explanation: Meaning: The calibration line could not be sent correctly from the microcontroller to the PC.<newline/>Reason: (difo) transmission error 	<newline/>Cure: Check the data transmission (via difo) and the data storage on the PC and in the microcontroller. Retry the data transmission.

description: The A/D converters were not armed for the next scan.
explanation: Meaning: The A/D converters were not armed for the next scan.<newline/>Reason: The corresponding software routine was not performed correctly.	<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding software routine, reset the system and arm the A/D converters again.

description: The D/A converters were not armed for the next scan.
explanation: Meaning: The D/A converters were not armed for the next scan.<newline/>Reason: The corresponding software routine was not performed correctly.	<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding software routine, reset the system and arm the D/A converters again.

description: The received event cannot be handled in the actual ScannerControl state.
explanation: <newline/>Meaning: The received event cannot be handled in the actual ScannerControl state. The event and the state can be seen in the event logging.<newline/>Reason: An event was sent at the wrong time to the Scanner Control <newline/>Cure: Verify that the event is sent to the correct state of the ScannerControl state table.

description: The adjustment of the A/D converter offsets failed.
explanation: Meaning: The adjustment of the A/D converter offsets failed.<newline/>Reason: The number of adjustment iterations exceeded the allowed maximum level. 	<newline/>Cure: Verify the data collected during the procedure to find (i) configuration errors before each scan, or (ii) hardware problems.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error it has to be analyzed by the SW developer.

description: The upper limit of the EEPROM(LLS) address range was exceeded when trying to access the device.
explanation: Meaning: The upper limit of the EEPROM(LLS) address range was exceeded when trying to access the device.<newline/>Reason: A wrong EEPROM(LLS) address was set (via the external control or by a software routine). 	<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the input value, and/or (ii) the corresponding software routine
column5: reset the system and access the EEPROM(LLS) again.

description: The test of accessing the modules failed.
explanation: Meaning: The test of accessing the modules failed.<newline/>Reason: At least one of the electronic devices (EEPROM (CCD or LLS), A/D converters, D/A converters, PLD, LLS) could not be accessed. 	<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the data set used by the SW to access the devices, (ii) the hardware (i.e. determine more specifically the electronic devices that cause problems)
column5: <newline/>Reset the system and try to access the device again.

description: The initialization of the scanning modules failed.
explanation: Meaning: The initialization of the scanning modules failed.<newline/>Reason: At least one of the electronic devices (EEPROM (CCD or LLS), A/D converters, D/A converters, PLD, LLS, FPGA) could not be initialized. 	<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the data set used by the SW to initialize the devices, (ii) the hardware (i.e. determine more specifically the electronic devices that cause problems)
column5: <newline/>Reset the system and try to initialize the devices again.

description: The verification of the normalization of the A/D converter amplification levels failed.
explanation: Meaning: The verification of the normalization of the A/D converter amplification levels failed.		<newline/>Reason: The normalized data set is not accurate enough. 	<newline/>Cure: (i) Load the normalized data set to the PC (using the Stratus Labor Client) and check the data set. (ii) Check the hardware on the basis of the result of (i) (epsecially the A/D converters).<newline/>Service:  Call the support center (same procedure as for error 2560).

description: The value of the A/D converter channel number is is not in the specified range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the A/D converter channel numberis not in the specified range.<newline/>Reason: A wrong channel number has been set.<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines with respect to handling the A/D converter channel numbers.

description: malloc() failed for generation of a data envelope in case of a timeout condition.
explanation: Meaning: malloc() failed for generation of data envelope in case of a timeout condition.<newline/>Reason: A problem with the memory allocation.<newline/>Cure: Check the memory allocation management.

description: queue_pend() returned with no envelope and no timeout condition applies.
explanation: Meaning: queue_pend() returned with no envelope and no timeout condition applies.<newline/>Reason: (i) The corresponding time out was not set correctly, or (ii) the corresponding message (event) did not reach the mailbox.<newline/>Cure: Check the time out set for a specific event and the mechanism for sending the event.

description: The value of the microcontroller port number is not in the specified range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the microcontroller port number is not in the specified range.<newline/>Reason: A wrong port number has been set.<newline/>Cure: Check the SW routines with respect to handling the port numbers.

description: The flex board is not connected to the distribution board.
explanation: Meaning: The flex board is not connected to the distribution board.<newline/>Reason: --<newline/>Cure: Check the cable connection.

description: The power supply cable is not connected to the distribution board.
explanation: Meaning: The power supply cable is not connected to the distribution board.<newline/>Reason: --<newline/>Cure: Check the cable connection.

description: The SHI board is not connected to the distribution board.
explanation: Meaning: The SHI board is not connected to the distribution board.<newline/>Reason: --<newline/>Cure: Check the cable connection.

description: The value of the supply voltage of the SHI Board is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the supply voltage of the SHI Board is out of the required range (8 V ± 3 %).<newline/>Reason: (i) voltage smaller than 8V - 3%: supply voltage not high enough, (ii) voltage greater than 8V + 3%: defect in the power supply unit, (iii) if all the monitored voltages of the SHI board are either too big or too small: the reference voltage is not correct.<newline/>Cure: Check the hardware according to one of the above mentioned three error reasons.<newline/>Service:  Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the SHI board), (ii) the SHI board.

description: The value of the Layout Module output voltage is out of the  required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the Layout Module output voltage is out of the required range (3.3 V ± 3 %).<newline/>Reason: (i) voltage smaller than 3.3V - 3%: supply voltage not high enough, (ii) voltage greater than 3.3V + 3%: defect in the voltage regulator, (iii) if all the monitored voltages of the SHI board are either too big or too small: the reference voltage is not correct.<newline/>Cure: Check the hardware according to one of the above mentioned three error reasons.<newline/>Service:  Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the SHI board), (ii) the SHI board.

description: The value of the FPGA supply voltage is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the FPGA supply voltage is out of the required range (2.5 V ± 3 %).<newline/>Reason: (i) voltage smaller than 2.5V - 3%: supply voltage not high enough, (ii) voltage greater than 2.5V + 3%: defect in the voltage regulator at the FPGA, (iii) if all the monitored voltages of the SHI board are either too big or too small: the reference voltage is not correct.<newline/>Cure: Check the hardware according to one of the above mentioned three error reasons.<newline/>Service:  Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the SHI board), (ii) the SHI board.

description: The value of the voltage for the CCD optocouplers is out of the  required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the voltage for the CCD optocouplers is out of the  required range (5 V ± 3 %).<newline/>Reason: (i) voltage smaller than 5V - 3%: supply voltage not high enough or defect in the fire wire, (ii) voltage greater than 5V + 3%: defect in the voltage regulator, (iii) if all the monitored voltages of the SHI board are either too big or too small: the reference voltage is not correct.<newline/>Cure: Check the hardware according to one of the above mentioned three error reasons.<newline/>Service:  Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the SHI board), (ii) the SHI board.

description: The normalized A/D amplification levels were not loaded from the EEPROM on the CCD board and therefore the default values are used.
explanation: Meaning: The normalized A/D amplification levels were not loaded from the EEPROM on the CCD board and therefore the default values are used.  It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.<newline/>Reason: (i) the EEPROM was not accessible, (ii) wrong header type, (iii) wrong header version. One of these three reasons is denoted as second error in the logged error message.<newline/>Cure: (i) check the data set stored in the EEPROM(CCD) (ii) if the data set is correct, load it again (iii) If the data set is not correct, perform the normalization and store the new data set.<newline/>Service:  Call the support center.

description: The normalized A/D amplification levels were not loaded from the EEPROM on the CCD board and therefore the default values are used. It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the detection mode is not defined (0: cw mode, 1: pulsed mode with 50 % duty cycle, 2: pulsed mode with adjustable duty cycle<newline/>Reason: A wrong detection mode number has been set.<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines with respect to handling the detection mode number.

description: A sector of the EEPOM(CCD) was not erased with in the defined time delay.
explanation: Meaning: A sector of the EEPOM(CCD) was not erased with in the defined time delay.<newline/>Reason: Hardware problem.<newline/>Cure: Reset the system and try the operation again. In case of repeated failure check the hardware.

description: The value of the detection time is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the detection time is out of the  required range. <newline/>Reason: A wrong detection time value has been set.<newline/>Cure: (i) Check the value input via the Stratus Labor Client. (ii) Check the corresponding SW routines with respect to handling the detection time.

description: The value of the duty cycle is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the detection time is out of the  required range. <newline/>Reason: A wrong duty cycle time value has been set.<newline/>Cure: (i) Check the value input via the Stratus Labor Client. (ii) Check the corresponding SW routines with respect to handling the duty cycle.

description: The value of the digital amplification is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the digital amplification is out of the required range. The index of the corresponding CCD sensor is given in the error message<newline/>Reason: An error has ocurred in the calculation of the matching factors.		<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the normalized amplification leveles selected for the scan, and (ii) the calculation of the matching factors.

description: The value of the base address is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the base address (for storing the calibration line data) is out of the required range. <newline/>Reason: A wrong base address has been set.		 <newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines with respect to setting the base address.

description: The number for selecting one of the two D/A converters is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The number for selecting one of the two D/A converters is not defined.<newline/>Reason: A wrong selection number has been set. 	<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines with respect to handling the D/A converter selection number.

description: The spread of the offset adjusted before the scan is too big.
explanation: Meaning: The spread of the offset adjusted before the scan is too big. The index of the corresponding CCD sensor is given in the warning message.<newline/>Reason: (i) Some light fell on the CCD sensors during the offset adjustment. (ii) A CCD sensor does not operate correctly.	 <newline/>Cure: (i) Check if some light may have fallen on the CCD sensors during the offset adjustment. (ii) Check the CCD sensors.

description: The FPGA initialization failed because the  CAS_LATENCY value is not supported.
explanation: Meaning: The FPGA initialization failed because the  CAS_LATENCY value is not supported.<newline/>Reason: A wrong CAS_LATENCY value has been set.<newline/>Cure: Correct the CAS_LATENCY value.<newline/>Service:  Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace the SHI board.

description: The FPGA initialization failed because BURST_LENGTH value is not supported.
explanation: Meaning: The FPGA initialization failed because the  BURST_LENGTH value is not supported.<newline/>Reason: A wrong BURST_LENGTH value has been set.<newline/>Cure: Correct the BURST_LENGTH value.<newline/>Service:  Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace the SHI board.

description: The FPGA initialization failed because the SDRAM controller does not start.
explanation: Meaning: The FPGA initialization failed because the SDRAM controller does not start.<newline/>Reason: There is (probably) no external clock signal for the FPGA (this cannot be verified by the software).<newline/>Cure: Check the harware with respect to the external clock signal and restart the system.<newline/>Service:  Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace the SHI board.

description: The FPGA test failed because the FPGA  is not loaded yet.
explanation: Meaning: The FPGA test failed because the FPGA  is not loaded yet.<newline/>Reason: see above<newline/>Cure: Load the FPGA and restart it.<newline/>Service:  Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace the SHI board.

description: The FPGA pattern generation failed because FPGA is not loaded yet.
explanation: Meaning: The pattern generator is not part of the actual FPGA version. The FPGA pattern generation failed because FPGA is not loaded yet.<newline/>Reason: --<newline/>Cure: -- This error code is momentarily not used.

description: The FPGA pattern generation failed because a flush FIFO underrun occured.
explanation: Meaning: The pattern generator is not part of the actual FPGA version. The FPGA pattern generation failed because flush FIFO underrun occured.<newline/>Reason: --<newline/>Cure: -- This error code is momentarily not used.

description: The FPGA pattern generation failed because a flush FIFO overflow occured.
explanation: Meaning: The pattern generator is not part of the actual FPGA version. The FPGA pattern generation failed because the flush FIFO overflow occured.<newline/>Reason: --<newline/>Cure: --  This error code is momentarily not used.

description: The FPGA pattern generation failed because the flush FIFO cannot be drained.
explanation: Meaning: The pattern generator is not part of the actual FPGA version. The FPGA pattern generation failed because the flush FIFO cannot be drained.<newline/>Reason: --<newline/>Cure: --  This error code is momentarily not used.

description: The flush FIFO cannot be drained.
explanation: Meaning: The flush FIFO cannot be drained.<newline/>Reason: HW problem<newline/>Cure: Check the hardware.<newline/>Service: Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the SHI board, (ii)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (iii) the ScanHead.

description: Ther FPGA test failed (one of the RAM's was not correctly accessible).
explanation: Meaning: The FPGA test failed (one of the RAM's was not correctly accessible).<newline/>Reason: see above<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding hardware.<newline/>Service: Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the SHI board, (ii)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (iii) the ScanHead.

description: The scan fifo write pump did not fill the scan fifo with SDRAM data.
explanation: Meaning:The scan fifo write pump did not fill the scan fifo with SDRAM data, fatal error.<newline/>Reason: Hardware problem.<newline/>Cure: Check the hardware.<newline/>Service: Restart the system (Digitizer and PC). If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the SHI board, (ii)  the three cables between the SHI board and the ScanHead (i.e. SHI board - distribution board, distribution board - ScanHeadControl board, ScanHeadControl board - ScanHead), (iii) the ScanHead.

description: The test of the LLS supply voltage failed in the active mode (i.e. with the LLS turned on). It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The test of the LLS supply voltage failed in the active mode (i.e. with the LLS turned on). The value of this voltage should be 8V. It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.<newline/>Reason: The power supply unit is defective.<newline/>Cure: Check the power supply voltage (and the LLS hardware).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead.

description: The test of the LLS supply voltage failed in the standby mode (i.e. with the LLS turned off). It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The test of the LLS supply voltage failed in the standby mode (i.e. with the LLS turned off). The value of this voltage should be 8V. It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.<newline/>Reason: The power supply unit is defective.<newline/>Cure: Check the power supply voltage (and the LLS hardware).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead.

description: The test of the LLS supply voltage failed in both modes (standby mode (i.e. with the LLS  turned off) and active mode (i.e. with the LLS  turned off). It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The test of the LLS supply voltage failed in both modes (standby mode (i.e. with the LLS  turned off) and active mode (i.e. with the LLS  turned off). It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.<newline/>Reason: The power supply unit is defective.<newline/>Cure: Check the power supply voltage (and the LLS hardware).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead.

description: The calibration of the (flight control) mechanics failed or an error occurred during the secomd half of the (scanning unit) startup procedure.
explanation: Meaning: The calibration of the (flight control) mechanics failed or an error occurred during the secomd half of the (scanning unit) startup procedure.<newline/>Reason: See subsequent error code. <newline/>Cure: See subsequent error code.

description: malloc() failed for the generation of a data envelope.
explanation: Meaning: malloc() failed for the generation of data envelope.<newline/>Reason: A problem with the memory allocation.<newline/>Cure: Check the memory allocation with respect to the communication envelopes.

description: malloc() failed for generation of a command envelope.
explanation: Meaning: malloc() failed for generation of a command envelope.<newline/>Reason: A problem with the memory allocation.<newline/>Cure: Check the memory allocation with respect to the communication envelopes.

description: malloc() failed for generation of an ICN envelope.
explanation: Meaning: malloc() failed for generation of an ICN envelope.<newline/>Reason: A problem with the memory allocation.<newline/>Cure: Check the memory allocation with respect to the communication envelopes.

description: A data envelope could not be delivered.
explanation: Meaning: A data envelope could not be delivered.<newline/>Reason: Problem with (i) the receiver, (ii) sending the envelope via the communication network (hardware or software).		 <newline/>Cure: Check the processing of the envelope by the postoffice (starting with the error messages).

description: A command envelope could not be delivered.
explanation: Meaning: A command envelope could not be delivered.<newline/>Reason: Problem with (i) the receiver, (ii) sending the envelope via the communication network (hardware or software).		 <newline/>Cure: Check the processing of the envelope by the postoffice (starting with the error messages).

description: An ICN envelope could not be delivered.
explanation: Meaning: An ICN envelope could not be delivered.<newline/>Reason: Problem with (i) the receiver, (ii) sending the envelope via the communication network (hardware or software).		 <newline/>Cure: Check the processing of the envelope by the postoffice (starting with the error messages).

description: The maximum number of iteration for the offset adjustment was exceeded.
explanation: Meaning: The maximum number of iterations for the offset adjustment was exceeded.<newline/>Reason: (i) Some light fell on the CCD sensors during the offset adjustment. (ii) A CCD sensor does not operate correctly. (iii) The data path does not work correctly.<newline/>Cure: (i) Check if some light may have fallen on the CCD sensors during the offset adjustment. (ii) Check the hardware (CCD sensors, data path).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same warning message the error has to be analyzed by the SW developer.

description: A parameter value could not be returned correctly.
explanation: Meaning: A parameter value could not be returned correctly. <newline/>Reason: (i) Communication problems, or (ii) the parmeter was retrieved in the wrong state of the SCC state table, or (iii) a wrong index was passed from ScannerControlProxy to ScannerControl (i.e. the command could not be interpreted).<newline/>Cure: Verify the communication, the SCC state and retrieve the parameter value again.

description: An external request for executing a command could not be carried out.
explanation: Meaning: An external request for executing a command could not be carried out.<newline/>Reason: (i) Communication problems, or (ii) the parmeter was retrieved in the wrong state of the SCC state table, or (iii) a wrong index was passed from ScannerControlProxy to ScannerControl (i.e. the command could not be interpreted).<newline/>Cure: Verify the communication, the SCC state and send the command again.

description: The upper limit of the number of the steps for incrementing the LLS voltage has been exceeded (and therefore the LLS voltage adjustment has failed).
explanation: Meaning: The upper limit of the number of the steps for incrementing the LLS voltage has been reached (and therefore the LLS voltage adjustment has failed).<newline/>Reason: The maximum voltage level is not sufficient for the operation of the LLS <newline/>Cure: Check the LLS hardware.

description: The signal level is  smaller than the previously set offset  level (and therefore the normalization procedure cannot be accomplished).
explanation: Meaning: The signal level (provided by the CDS generator) is  smaller than the previously set offset  level (and therefore the normalization procedure cannot be accomplished).<newline/>Reason: (i) The signal level or the offset level were not generated correctly. (ii) The offset level was not well set with the corresponding software algorithm.<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the hardware on the CCD board, and (ii) the corresponding software algorithm.

description: The ScannerControl did not get the correct scan delay value from SlowScanControl.
explanation: Meaning: The ScannerControl did not get the correct scan delay value from SlowScanControl. The value is given in the error message.<newline/>Reason: (i) The scan delay value was too big, or (ii) The response code was not correct.<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding communication.

description: The Begin of Scan and the Begin Of Line were not detected. This may cause image quality problems. It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The BOS (begin of scan) and the BOL (begin of line) were not detected.  This may cause image quality problems. It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.<newline/>Reason: (i) The BOL/BOS detection time out was not big enough, or (ii) The BOS LED does not work or the current value was not high enough, or (iii) the optical system for detecting BOL/BOS is not set up correctly (this may include the IP).<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the value of the BOL/BOS detection time out, (ii) the BOS LED and the BOS LED current value, (iii) the optical system for detecting BOL/BOS.

description: The ScannerControl did not get the correct BOL/BOS detection time out value from SlowScanControl. Therefore the default value is used.
explanation: Meaning: The ScannerControl did not get the correct BOL/BOS detection time out value from SlowScanControl. Therefore the default value is used. The value is given in the error message.<newline/>Reason: (i) The value of the BOL/BOS detection time out was not in the required range, or (ii) The response code was not correct.<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding communication.

description: An external request for performing a test function or setting a test parametercould not be carried out.
explanation: Meaning: An external request for performing a test function or setting a test parameter could not be carried out.<newline/>Reason: (i) Communication problems, or (ii) the parmeter was retrieved in the wrong state of the SCC state table, or (iii) a wrong index was passed from ScannerControlSecondProxy to ScannerControl (i.e. the command could not be interpreted).<newline/>Cure: Verify the communication, the SCC state and send the command again.

description: The input operation code was too big. The  operation code was set to the default value.
explanation: Meaning: The input  operation code was too big. The  operation code was set to the default value (GenRad).<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: -

description: The FPGA cannot be accessed correctly.
explanation: Meaning: The FPGA cannot be accessed correctly. <newline/>Reason: There has been an FPGA bus error indicating a time out of a former FPGA access.	 <newline/>Cure: Restart the system and retry the accesses. This error code is not used any more.

description: The CAN voltage is either not turned on or has a too small value.
explanation: Meaning: The CAN voltage is either not turned on or has a too small value.<newline/>Reason: (i) The cable to the CAN voltage supply is defective, or (ii) the corresponding relais on the board	is defective. <newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding hardware.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the cable between the SHI board and the CAN voltage supply, (ii) the SHI board.

description: The mailbox for supervising the PLD access contains an undefined message.
explanation: Meaning: The mailbox for supervising the PLD access contains an undefined message.<newline/>Reason: Error in the locking mechanism of the PLD.<newline/>Cure: Check the locking mechanism and the acesses to the PLD. This error code is momentarily not used.

description: The lenght of the data transferred to PLDAccess for transmission to the PLD is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The lenght of the data transferred to PLDAccess for transmission to the PLD is out of the required range.<newline/>Reason: SW error of a unit transferring data to the PLDAccess<newline/>Cure: Check the data transferred to PLDAccess. This error code is momentarily not used.

description: The value of the supply voltage of the analog electronics on the CCD board is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the supply voltage of the analog electronics on the CCD board is out of the required range (nominal value 8V, range: > 7V).<newline/>Reason: Error of the corresponding power supply.<newline/>Cure: Check the CCD board hardware with respect to the supply voltage of the analog electronics.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead.

description: The value of the supply voltage of the digital electronics on the CCD board is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the supply voltage of the digital electronics on the CCD board is out of the required range (nominal value 8V, range: > 7V).<newline/>Reason: The corresponding power supply is defective.<newline/>Cure: Check the CCD board hardware with respect to the supply voltage of the digital electronics.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead.

description: The value of the supply voltage of the CCD interface board is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the supply voltage of the CCD interface board is out of the required range  (nominal value 18V, range: > 17V).<newline/>Reason: The corresponding power supply is defective.<newline/>Cure: Check the CCD board hardware with respect to the supply voltage of the CCD interface.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead.

description: The value of the supply voltage of the operational amplifier on the CCD board is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the supply voltage of the operational amplifier on the CCD board is out of the required range     (nominal value -1V, range: smaller than - 1V).<newline/>Reason: The corresponding power supply is defective.<newline/>Cure: Check the CCD board hardware with respect to the supply voltage of the operational amplifier.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace successively (i) the power supply (and the cabling between the power supply and the ScanHead), (ii) the ScanHead.

description: The LLS operation point is not adjusted correctly. It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The LLS operation point is not adjusted correctly. It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.<newline/>Reason: The voltage supply of the operation point regulation is not sufficiently high.<newline/>Cure: Check the LLS  hardware with respect to the LLS operation point.

description: The write/read test of the SDRAM failed.
explanation: Meaning: The write/read test of the SDRAM failed
column5: at least one test value was not writtten into or read out of the SDRAM correctly.<newline/>Reason: There is a defect in the SDRAM.<newline/>Cure: Check the SDRAM (hardware).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the SHI board.

description: The scan head did not reach the focus level before the BOL/BOS detection was started.
explanation: Meaning: The scan head did not reach the focus level before the BOL/BOS detection was started. This may also be the case for the ensuing scan.<newline/>Reason: Communication problem (it was somehow slowed down).<newline/>Cure: Find out what (mechanism) has slowed down the communication, so that the flight control could not act fastly enough.

description: The maximum measured A/D converter amplificationn level is zero.
explanation: Meaning: The maximum measured A/D converter amplificationn level is zero and therefore the normalization process cannot be accomplished.<newline/>Reason: (i) Hardware problem (A/D converters), (ii) Software problem during the normailzation process.<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the hardware (A/D converters), and (ii) the corresponding software routines.

description: The time delay for the begin of scan has a wrong value.
explanation: Meaning: The time delay for the begin of scan has a wrong value.  In this case the default value is used. The abslute value of the time delay is given as parameter in the log message.<newline/>Reason: A timing error occured during the handling of the BOS detection event.<newline/>Cure: Check the queue handling mechanism and the communication timing with respect to the BOS detection event.

description: The basic write test of the EEPROM on the CCD board failed. Reading from the device may still work (the data read from the device is verified separately). It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The basic write test of the EEPROM on the CCD board failed. Reading from the device may still work (the data read from the device is verified separately). It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.<newline/>Reason: (i) The device is defect (reading from the device may still work). (ii)	The communication between the microcontroller and the EEPROM on the CCD board does not work correctly.<newline/>Cure: Retry the basic write test of the EEPROM(CCD)
column5: if the test then still does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).<newline/>Service: This is only a warning message. (i) As long as no data is written into the device (e.g. calibration lines) no problems will arise because the data read out of the device (during the start-up) is verified separately. Normal use of the device is possible. (ii) If a calibration has to be done (which implies that data has to be written into the device) the ScanHead has to be replaced before.

description: A sector of the EEPROM on the CCD board has not been erased.
explanation: Meaning: A sector of the EEPROM on the CCD board has not been erased (e.g. before writing data). <newline/>Reason: (i) The communication between the microcontroller and the EEPROM on the CCD board does not work correctly. (ii) The device or the cabling are defective.<newline/>Cure: Retry the basic write/read test of the EEPROM(CCD)
column5: if the test does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).

description: Data was not written into a sector of the EEPROM (CCD).
explanation: Meaning: Data was not written into a sector of the EEPROM (CCD). <newline/>Reason: The communication between the microcontroller and the EEPROM on the CCD board does not work correctly.<newline/>Cure: Retry the basic write/read test of the EEPROM(CCD)
column5: if the test does not work check the hardware (device and cabling).

description: The write pointer position after the scan is too low
explanation: the image has neither been scanned nor erased. Reset the system and scan the image plate again.
column5: Meaning: The write pointer position after the scan is too low
column6: the image has neither been scanned nor erased. Rest the system and scan the image plate again. The minimum pointer position is given as parameter in th log message (relative to the beginnning of the image).<newline/>Reason: (i) Not enough data was written into the SDRAM by the corresponding  hardware components (PLD, FPGA), (ii) ScannerControl received an an interrupt ('scan finished') although no scan was performed.<newline/>Cure: (i) The LLS is turned off in order to preserve the image on the IP.              (ii) The image can be scanned again after a reset of the system.

description: The D/A converter data was not loaded from the EEPROM on the CCD board and therefore the default values are used. It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.
explanation: Meaning: The D/A converter data was not loaded from the EEPROM on the CCD board and therefore the default values are used.  It is still possible to scan but the Service should be informed.<newline/>Reason: The header of the data set had wrong values.	<newline/>Cure: Check the data set stored in the EEPROM(CCD), correct the wrong values and load the data again.<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the ScanHead.

description: Scanner Control has received a response which cannot be handled.
explanation: Meaning: Scanner Control has received a response which cannot be handled. The sender is given as parameter in the log message.<newline/>Reason: Communication error.		<newline/>Cure: Check the communication with/of the unit that sent the response.

description: The IP type set is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: The IP type set is not defined.<newline/>Reason: Communication of SW  error.		<newline/>Cure: Check the communication with/of the unit that se(n)t the IP type.

description: The command is not defined or cannot be handled in the actual state.
explanation: Meaning: The command is not defined or cannot be handled in the actual state. The command number is given as parameter in the error message.<newline/>Reason: ScannerControl obtained a wrong command and did not or could not handle it correctly.     <newline/>Cure: Check (i) the sender of the wrong command, and (ii) the handling of the wrong event (command).

description: The check sum of the LD values is not correct.
explanation: Meaning: The check sum of the LD values (preliminary and operational currents) is not correct.<newline/>Reason: The data has not been read out of the EEPROM (LLS) correctly. <newline/>Cure: Check the LD data (i) read out of the EEPROM (LLS) and (ii) written into the info counter data.

description: The check sum of the D/A converter values is not correct.
explanation: Meaning: The check sum of the D/A converter values (anti-blooming and reset register) is not correct.<newline/>Reason: The data has not been read out correctly. <newline/>Cure: Check the D/A converter data (i) read out of the EEPROM (CCD) and (ii) written into the info counter data.

description: The check sum of the scannersensitivity factors is not correct.
explanation: Meaning: The check sum of the scannersensitivity factors is not correct.<newline/>Reason: The data has not been read out correctly. <newline/>Cure: Check the scanner sensitivity factors (i) read out of the EEPROM (CCD) and (ii) written into the info counter data.

description: The index of the A/D converter amplification level does not have a correct value.
explanation: Meaning: The index of the A/D converter amplification level does not have a correct value. This verification is done during reading the data out of the EEPROM (CCD). The level index is given as parameter in the warning message.<newline/>Reason: The data has not been stored or read out correctly. <newline/>Cure: Verify the normalized data stored in the EEPROM (CCD) (using the Stratus Labor Client). If the verification shows errors:  (i) normalize the amplification levels again (ii) store a correct data set in the EEPROM (CCD) (iii) load the data set from the EEPROM (CCD) and verify it. In this way possible SW or HW errors can be detected.

description: The input speed class value was too big. The speed class was set to the biggest possible value.
explanation: Meaning: The input speed class value was too big. The speed class was set to the highest possible value.<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: --

description: The input speed class value was too small. The speed class was set to the smallest possible value.
explanation: Meaning: The input speed class value was too small. The speed class was set to the smallest possible value.<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: --

description: The FPGA version is not correct.
explanation: Meaning: The FPGA version is not correct.<newline/>Reason: The wrong FPGA version was loaded<newline/>Cure: Load the correct version.<newline/>Service: Reload the SW of the SHI board. If the error still occurs, the SW version of the FPGA has to be verified by the corresponding SW developer.

description: The input value of the LD intensity range was too big. The LD intensity range was set to the biggest possible value.
explanation: Meaning: The input value of the LD intensity range was too big. The LD intensity range was set to the biggest possible value.<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: --

description: The input correction mode value was too big. The correction mode was set to the biggest possible value.
explanation: Meaning: The input correction mode value was too big. The correction mode was set to the biggest possible value.<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: --

description: The input IP thickness value was too small. The IP thickness was set to the smallest possible value.
explanation: Meaning: The input IP thickness value was too small. The IP thickness was set to the smallest possible value.<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: --

description: The input IP thickness value was too big. The IP thickness was set to the biggest possible value.
explanation: Meaning: The input IP thickness value was too big. The IP thickness was set to the biggest possible value.<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: --

description: No response was obtained from the unit SlowScanControl within the defined time out.
explanation: Meaning: No response was obtained from the unit SlowScanControl within the defined time out.<newline/>Reason: (i) Communication problems (e.g. CAN), (ii) Problem of the corresponding node or task.<newline/>Cure: Check the communication and the activities of the node /task (e.g. via the logging information).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same warning message the error has to be analyzed by the SW developer.

description: No response was obtained from the unit FlightControl within the defined time out.
explanation: Meaning: No response was obtained from the unit FlightControl within the defined time out.<newline/>Reason: (i) Communication problems (e.g. CAN), (ii) Problem of the corresponding node or task.<newline/>Cure: Check the communication and the activities of the corresponding node /task (e.g. via the logging information).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same warning message the error has to be analyzed by the SW developer.

description: No response was obtained from the unit TransportIP within the defined time out.
explanation: Meaning: No response was obtained from the unit TransportIP within the defined time out.<newline/>Reason: (i) Communication problems (e.g. CAN), (ii) Problem of the corresponding node or task.<newline/>Cure: Check the communication and the activities of the corresponding node /task (e.g. via the logging information).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same warning message the error has to be analyzed by the SW developer.

description: No response was obtained from the unit PowerSupply within the defined time out.
explanation: Meaning: No response was obtained from the unit PowerSupply within the defined time out.<newline/>Reason: (i) Communication problems (e.g. CAN), (ii) Problem of the corresponding node or task.<newline/>Cure: Check the communication and the activities of the corresponding node /task (e.g. via the logging information).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same warning message the error has to be analyzed by the SW developer.

description: ROILeft has a negative value.
explanation: Meaning: ROILeft has a negative value. It should only have non-negative values. The absolute value of ROILeft is given as parameter in the corresponding warning message<newline/>Reason: A wrong pixel has been given by the BOL detection.<newline/>Cure: A corresponding error handling is done by the software. Thereby ROILeft keeps the default value.

description: The value of ROILeft is too big.
explanation: Meaning: The value of ROI Left is too big. The value is given as parameter in the warning message.<newline/>Reason: A wrong pixel has been given by the BOL detection.<newline/>Cure: A corresponding error handling is done by the software. Thereby ROILeft is set to zero.

description: The value of the BOL  pixel determined by the FPGA is too big.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the BOL  pixel determined by the FPGA is too big. The value is given as parameter in the warning message.<newline/>Reason: Hardware problem (FPGA).<newline/>Cure: A corresponding error handling is done by the software. Thereby the BOLBOSNotchPixel  keeps the default value. Moreover, the hardware has to be checked.

description: The value of the BOL  pixel determined by the FPGA is too small.
explanation: Meaning: The value of the BOL  pixel determined by the FPGA is too small. The value is given as parameter in the warning message.<newline/>Reason: Hardware problem (FPGA).<newline/>Cure: A corresponding error handling is done by the software. Thereby the BOLBOSNotchPixel keeps the default value. Moreover, the hardware has to be checked.

description: The temperature could not be determined.
explanation: Meaning: The temperature could not be determined. <newline/>Reason: See explanation of the 'previous error' given in the log mesaage.<newline/>Cure: --

description: The number of the temperature sensor is not defined.
explanation: Meaning: <newline/>The number for selecting one of the two  temperature sensors is not defined.<newline/>Reason: A wrong selection number has been set. 	<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding SW routines and set the correct selection number.

description: The temperature conversion was not started (by the temperature sensor).
explanation: Meaning: The temperature conversion was not started (by the temperature sensor).<newline/>Reason: (i) Software error, (ii) error of the PLD, (iii) error of the device (hardware problem).<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the software (and the PLD) with respect to the communication with the temperature sensor, (ii) the temperature sensor.

description: The byte reception of the temperature sensor was not acknowledged.
explanation: Meaning: The byte reception of the temperature sensor was not acknowledged.<newline/>Reason: (i) Software error, (ii) error of the PLD, (iii) error of the device (hardware problem).<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the software (and the PLD) with respect to the communication with the temperature sensor, (ii) the temperature sensor.

description: The semaphore for accesing the PLD was not set free within the defined time out.
explanation: Meaning: The semaphore for accesing the PLD was not set free within the defined time out.<newline/>Reason: (i) The PLD access was locked too long by another unit. (ii) An error ocurred in the semaphore handling<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the access to the PLD by the different units, and (ii) the semaphore handling.

description: The write/read test of the RDRRAM failed.
explanation: Meaning: The write/read test of the RDRRAM failed
column5: at least one test value was not writtten into or read out of the RDRRAM correctly.<newline/>Reason: There is a defect in the RDRRAM<newline/>Cure: Check the RDRRAM (hardware).<newline/>Service: Restart the Digitizer. If there is still the same error replace the SHI board.

description: malloc() failed for generation of an IP transp envelope.
explanation: Meaning: malloc() failed for generation of an IP transp envelope.<newline/>Reason: A problem with the memory allocation.<newline/>Cure: Check the memory allocation with respect to the communication envelopes.

description: An IP Transp envelope could not be delivered.
explanation: Meaning: An IP Transp envelope could not be delivered.<newline/>Reason: Problem with (i) the receiver, (ii) sending the envelope via the communication network (hardware or software).		 <newline/>Cure: Check the processing of the envelope by the postoffice (starting with the error messages).

description: The command ID is out of range in the add_callback operation for command envelopes.
explanation: Meaning: The command ID is out of range in the add_callback operation for command envelopes. The erroneous command ID is given in the log message as parameter.<newline/>Reason: Software error.	 <newline/>Cure: Check the software with respect to the indices of the command IDs (add_callback operation, task calling the add_callback operation, corresponding 'pdml'-files).

description: The command ID is out of range in the add_callback operation for data envelopes.
explanation: Meaning: The command ID is out of range in the add_callback operation for data envelopes. The erroneous command ID is given in the log message as parameter.<newline/>Reason: Software error.	 <newline/>Cure: Check the software with respect to the indices of the command IDs (add_callback operation, task calling the add_callback operation, corresponding 'pdml'-files).

description: The command ID is out of range in the add_callback operation for ICN envelopes.
explanation: Meaning: The command ID is out of range in the add_callback operation for ICN (info counter) envelopes. The erroneous command ID is given in the log message as parameter.<newline/>Reason: Software error.	 <newline/>Cure: Check the software with respect to the indices of the command IDs (add_callback operation, task calling the add_callback operation, corresponding 'pdml'-files).

description: The command ID is out of range in the add_callback operation for IPTransp envelopes.
explanation: Meaning: The command ID is out of range in the add_callback operation for IPTransp envelopes. The erroneous command ID is given in the log message as parameter.<newline/>Reason: Software error.	 <newline/>Cure: Check the software with respect to the indices of the command IDs (add_callback operation, task calling the add_callback operation, corresponding 'pdml'-files).

description: The digital temperature output is out of the required range.
explanation: Meaning: The digital temperature output is out of the required range.<newline/>Reason: (i) Software error, (ii) error of the PLD, (iii) error of the device (hardware problem).<newline/>Cure: Check (i) the software (and the PLD) with respect to the communication with the temperature sensor, (ii) the temperature sensor.

description: The temperature on the CCD board exceeds the maximum value. This may cause problems with the image quality.
explanation: Meaning:The temperature on the CCD board exceeds the maximum value. This may cause problems with the image quality.<newline/>Reason: (i) The temperature regulation inside the machine does not work correctly.  <newline/>Cure: (i) Let the machine cool down. (ii) Check the temperature regulation inside the machine.

description: The input IP sensitivity value was too big. The IP sensitivity was set to the biggest possible value.
explanation: Meaning: The input IP sensitivity value was too big. The IP sensitivity was set to the biggest possible value.<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: --

description: The input IP sensitivity value was too small. The IP sensitivity was set to the smallest possible value.
explanation: Meaning:The input IP sensitivity value was too small. The IP sensitivity was set to the smallest possible value.<newline/>Reason: No error occured, the error code  is necessary for displaying the best fit notification.<newline/>Cure: --

description: The number of pixels written into the SDRAM during a scan is wrong.
explanation: Meaning:The number of pixels written into the SDRAM during a scan is wrong.<newline/>Reason: (i) The scan parameters were not set correctly, (ii) The hardware did not transmit the correct number of pixels into the SDRAM<newline/>Cure: Check the corresponding hard- and software (the exact number of pixels and the corresponding pointer positions are logged separately).

description: The address set in the RDR RAM before the scan is not zero.
explanation: Meaning:The address set in the RDR RAM before the scan is not zero. The RDR RAM address is logged as parameter in the corresponding error message.<newline/>Reason: The state of the RDR RAM is not 'idle'.<newline/>Cure: Check if the ESD-brush is mounted at the bottom of the machine (for discharging (connecting) the NIP).

description: Power Supply, No Infocounter Requestor ID found.
explanation: Module:  Power Supply Reason:  No valid infocounter Requestor ID found.<newline/>Meaning: Not able to send Infocounter Event<newline/>Cure:    call activateEvents() Proxy command first.

description: Power Supply, cannot deliver command from proxy to PS-task
explanation: Module:  Power Supply Meaning: Cannot send any command from PowerSupply-proxy to PowerSupply-task through PostOffice.<newline/>Cure: SW-Bugfixing

description: Power Supply, Switch on U Var 3.6V-6.8V failed
explanation: Module:  Power Supply Meaning: Switch on variable voltage 3.6V-6.8V for LineLightSource failed.<newline/>Cure: Change Power Supply Unit

description: Power Supply, U Var 3.6V-6.8V lost while scanning.
explanation: Module:  Power Supply Meaning: Variable voltage 3.6V-6.8V for LineLightSource break down while scanning.<newline/>Cure: Change Power Supply Unit

description: Power Supply, Switch on U Var 18V-30V failed
explanation: Module:  Power Supply Meaning: Switch on variable voltage 18V-30V for CCD-Node failed.<newline/>Cure: Change Power Supply Unit

description: Power Supply, U Var 18V-30V lost while scanning.
explanation: Module:  Power Supply Meaning: Variable voltage 18V-30V for CCD-Node break down while scanning.<newline/>Cure: Change Power Supply Unit

description: Power Supply, U Var 18V-30V status error.
